

    
        BEIJING, July 28(Xinhuanet)-- Yahoo China has begun to provide one gigabyte(GB) of e-mail storage free of charge, providing the largest-capacity e-mail storage in the country.  The increased storage capacity is open to all Internet users, according to a statement on the Yahoo China web site.  Yahoo e-mail service now has more than 500 million global users, said Zhou Hongyi, president of Yahoo China."The gigabyte age of e-mail storage is coming."  Some web companies based in China have enlarged storage for their e-mail boxes this year. Sina has upgraded to 30 megabytes(MB) and Netease up to 260 MB, the Beijing Daily Messenger reported.   Thanks to  urlLink Sina  for the information.  
    
    
